Real Madrid head coach, Zinedine Zidane, has released a 22-man squad to tackle Alavés in Friday’s La Liga fixture at the Estadio Alfredo Di Stefano Stadium. The Frenchman included forward, Eden Hazard in the squad to face Alavés after he omitted the former Chelsea from Real Madrid’s squads that defeated Getafe and Athletic Club respectively. Zidane announced the list in a post through the club’s official website. Zidane’s men head to the game after a 1-0 victory against Athletic Club in their previous La Liga encounter last weekend. Real Madrid squad against Alavés: Goalkeepers: Courtois, Areola and Altube. Defenders: Militão, Varane, Mendy, Javi Hernández and Miguel Gutiérrez. Midfielders: Kroos, Modric, Casemiro, Valverde and Isco. Forwards: Hazard, Benzema, Bale, Lucas Vázquez, Asensio, Brahim, Mariano, Vinicius Jr. and Rodrygo. The match is scheduled for 9 pm.